      def  remove_pattern(input_txt,pattern):
          r = re.findall(pattern,input_txt)
          for word in r:
              input_txt = re.sub(word,"",input_txt)
          return input_txt

      def hashtag_extract(tweet):
          hashtags = []
          for word in tweet:
              ht = re.findall(r"#(\w+)", word)
              hashtags.append(ht)
          return hashtags
      . . .
